honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class PrinterStatus_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterStatus_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PrinterStatus_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles Printer Statuses from the [SOH]a query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    1Interpreter Busy (Imaging)
    2Paper Out or Fault
    3Ribbon Out or Fault
    4Printing Batch
    5Busy Printing
    6Printer Paused
    7Label Presented
    8Rewinder Out or Fault
    9Cutter fault
    10Paper out
    11Ribbon Saver fault
    12Print head up
    13Top of form fault
    14Ribbon low
    17Printer Ready
    18Waiting for Signal
    19Waiting for Data
    20COM1 has data to be parsed
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • PrinterStatus_DPL

        public PrinterStatus_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
